The paper discusses heap abstractions for static analysis, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses summarization techniques based on logic (cs.LO) and instrumentation predicates (cs.CR), which are relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on creating new abstractions by mixing and matching models and summarization techniques is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
